<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><?xml-stylesheet type="text/xml" href="https://www.melquiadesaseron.com/feed.xslt.xml"?><feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><generator uri="https://jekyllrb.com/" version="4.3.2">Jekyll</generator><link href="https://www.melquiadesaseron.com/blog/feed.xml" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml"/><link href="https://www.melquiadesaseron.com/" rel="alternate" type="text/html"/><updated>2023-07-13T21:40:26+02:00</updated><id>https://www.melquiadesaseron.com/blog/feed.xml</id><title type="html">Melquiades Aseron III</title><subtitle>Customer Success · Global Mobility · Law</subtitle><author><name>Melquiades Aseron III</name></author><entry><title type="html">Fotos Dramáticas con Sketchbook</title><link href="https://www.melquiadesaseron.com/blog/2023/07/13/fotos-dramaticas-con-sketchbook/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Fotos Dramáticas con Sketchbook"/><published>2023-07-13T00:00:00+02:00</published><updated>2023-07-13T21:38:43+02:00</updated><id>https://www.melquiadesaseron.com/blog/2023/07/13/fotos-dramaticas-con-sketchbook</id><author><name>Melquiades Aseron III</name></author><category term="customer-success"/><category term="technology"/><category term="lgbt"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[After publishing my post about the Pride March here in A Coruña, I was so excited about a new discovery I made while writing it that I decided to share it here - that is, editing photos so that the important parts are highlighted in color using Sketchbook.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://www.melquiadesaseron.com/assets/images/blog/fotos-dramaticas-con-sketchbook-cover.jpg"/><media:content medium="image" url="https://www.melquiadesaseron.com/assets/images/blog/fotos-dramaticas-con-sketchbook-cover.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/"/></entry><entry><title type="html">Timesheets</title><link href="https://www.melquiadesaseron.com/blog/2023/07/06/timesheets/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Timesheets"/><published>2023-07-06T00:00:00+02:00</published><updated>2023-07-06T18:55:31+02:00</updated><id>https://www.melquiadesaseron.com/blog/2023/07/06/timesheets</id><author><name>Melquiades Aseron III</name></author><category term="customer-success"/><category term="history"/><category term="law"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Tools that track employee hours are ubiquitous in the world of work - whether one is a farm employee who has to punch in and out every working day, or a software developer who needs to track the the client projects that they’ve spent time on. Following a lively debate on this topic over brunch with friends, I decided to look into the value of these tools.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://www.melquiadesaseron.com/assets/images/blog/timesheets-cover.jpg"/><media:content medium="image" url="https://www.melquiadesaseron.com/assets/images/blog/timesheets-cover.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/"/></entry><entry><title type="html">Orgullo 2023 - A Coruña</title><link href="https://www.melquiadesaseron.com/blog/2023/06/30/orgullo-2023-a-coruna/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Orgullo 2023 - A Coruña"/><published>2023-06-30T00:00:00+02:00</published><updated>2023-07-02T09:33:21+02:00</updated><id>https://www.melquiadesaseron.com/blog/2023/06/30/orgullo-2023-a-coruna</id><author><name>Melquiades Aseron III</name></author><category term="lgbt"/><category term="history"/><category term="law"/><category term="psychology"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[June is Pride Month and the 28th is International Pride Day. Just like in many cities across the world, the LGBTQ+ community in A Coruña held a Pride March (Marcha de Orgullo Gay in Spanish) filled with rainbows that symbolize the diversity of the community and the colorful contributions they make to humanity.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://www.melquiadesaseron.com/assets/images/blog/orgullo-2023-a-coruna-cover.jpg"/><media:content medium="image" url="https://www.melquiadesaseron.com/assets/images/blog/orgullo-2023-a-coruna-cover.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/"/></entry><entry><title type="html">Noite de San Xoán</title><link href="https://www.melquiadesaseron.com/blog/2023/06/29/noite-de-san-xoan/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Noite de San Xoán"/><published>2023-06-29T00:00:00+02:00</published><updated>2023-06-29T16:49:12+02:00</updated><id>https://www.melquiadesaseron.com/blog/2023/06/29/noite-de-san-xoan</id><author><name>Melquiades Aseron III</name></author><category term="history"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[On the evening of the 23rd of June, the people of A Coruña gathers to celebrate one of the most important and cherished traditions of Galicia (along with the rest of Spain), with mystic bouquets, grilled sardines, bonfires and fireworks.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://www.melquiadesaseron.com/assets/images/blog/noite-de-san-xoan-cover.jpg"/><media:content medium="image" url="https://www.melquiadesaseron.com/assets/images/blog/noite-de-san-xoan-cover.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/"/></entry><entry><title type="html">Lupang Hinirang</title><link href="https://www.melquiadesaseron.com/blog/2023/06/22/lupang-hinirang/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Lupang Hinirang"/><published>2023-06-22T00:00:00+02:00</published><updated>2023-06-23T09:29:18+02:00</updated><id>https://www.melquiadesaseron.com/blog/2023/06/22/lupang-hinirang</id><author><name>Melquiades Aseron III</name></author><category term="music"/><category term="history"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Lupang Hinirang (Chosen Land) is the title of the Philippine National Anthem. The melody was composed by Julián Felipe and was originally called “Marcha Filipina Magdalo” before it was renamed “Marcha Nacional Filipina” and adopted as the national anthem of the newly proclaimed República Filipina (also known as the “República de Malolos”). The lyrics were then written by José Palma, a poet and revolutionary soldier, and were originally in Spanish.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://www.melquiadesaseron.com/assets/images/blog/lupang-hinirang-cover.jpg"/><media:content medium="image" url="https://www.melquiadesaseron.com/assets/images/blog/lupang-hinirang-cover.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/"/></entry><entry><title type="html">The Spanish Tortilla</title><link href="https://www.melquiadesaseron.com/blog/2023/06/21/the-spanish-tortilla/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="The Spanish Tortilla"/><published>2023-06-21T00:00:00+02:00</published><updated>2023-06-22T10:38:07+02:00</updated><id>https://www.melquiadesaseron.com/blog/2023/06/21/the-spanish-tortilla</id><author><name>Melquiades Aseron III</name></author><category term="cooking"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[A truly iconic Spanish dish, the tortilla de patatas is served as a tapa or a pincho (pintxo in the Basque Country) in bars or cooked at home as an easy-to-prepare meal. Except for a handful of techniques that I developed on my own, this is my husband Carlos’ recipe, which, in turn, was inspired by El Comidista’s. When cooked correctly, the dish is rich, flavorful, and creamy - I actually thought it contained cheese the first time I tried it.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://www.melquiadesaseron.com/assets/images/blog/the-spanish-tortilla-cover.jpg"/><media:content medium="image" url="https://www.melquiadesaseron.com/assets/images/blog/the-spanish-tortilla-cover.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/"/></entry><entry><title type="html">Deepfakes on Steroids - Netflix’s “Joan Is Awful”</title><link href="https://www.melquiadesaseron.com/blog/2023/06/19/netflix-joan-is-awful/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Deepfakes on Steroids - Netflix’s “Joan Is Awful”"/><published>2023-06-19T00:00:00+02:00</published><updated>2023-06-29T16:49:12+02:00</updated><id>https://www.melquiadesaseron.com/blog/2023/06/19/netflix-joan-is-awful</id><author><name>Melquiades Aseron III</name></author><category term="law"/><category term="motion-pictures"/><category term="technology"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Netflix has released Season 6 of the Black Mirror series, and its first episode “Joan Is Awful” definitely made the 4-year wait worthwhile as it once again weaved together worrisome developments over the last few years, such as deepfakes and artificial intelligence, into an over-the-top cautionary tale.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://www.melquiadesaseron.com/assets/images/blog/netflix-joan-is-awful-cover.jpg"/><media:content medium="image" url="https://www.melquiadesaseron.com/assets/images/blog/netflix-joan-is-awful-cover.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/"/></entry><entry><title type="html">BBVA’s Creative Crisis Response</title><link href="https://www.melquiadesaseron.com/blog/2023/06/18/bbva-creative-crisis-response/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="BBVA’s Creative Crisis Response"/><published>2023-06-18T00:00:00+02:00</published><updated>2023-06-22T10:38:07+02:00</updated><id>https://www.melquiadesaseron.com/blog/2023/06/18/bbva-creative-crisis-response</id><author><name>Melquiades Aseron III</name></author><category term="customer-success"/><category term="technology"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Yesterday, BBVA’s mobile app and website suffered a severe system issue which rendered it inaccessible for several hours.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://www.melquiadesaseron.com/assets/images/blog/bbva-creative-crisis-response-cover.jpg"/><media:content medium="image" url="https://www.melquiadesaseron.com/assets/images/blog/bbva-creative-crisis-response-cover.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/"/></entry><entry><title type="html">A Place for My Stories and Ideas</title><link href="https://www.melquiadesaseron.com/blog/2023/05/04/hello-world/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="A Place for My Stories and Ideas"/><published>2023-05-04T00:00:00+02:00</published><updated>2023-06-22T17:25:41+02:00</updated><id>https://www.melquiadesaseron.com/blog/2023/05/04/hello-world</id><author><name>Melquiades Aseron III</name></author><category term="meta"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Hello, world! I’m Mel, and I have stories to tell and ideas to share! I’ve been looking for a place to keep them and, thanks to my wonderful husband Carlos, I now have this cozy nook on the internet.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://www.melquiadesaseron.com/assets/images/blog/hello-world.jpg"/><media:content medium="image" url="https://www.melquiadesaseron.com/assets/images/blog/hello-world.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/"/></entry></feed>